parties.raw_snippet:
BETWEEN:
Paratek Pharmaceuticals, Inc., a company having a place of business at 75 Park Plaza, 4th Floor, Boston, MA 02116, USA (“Customer”)
AND:
CARBOGEN AMCIS AG, a company having a place of business at Hauptstrasse 171, CH 4416 Bubendorf, Switzerland (“Supplier” and, collectively
with Customer, the “Parties”, and each, a “Party).
parties.reasoning: The parties are explicitly listed in the “BETWEEN/AND” block identifying each company and role.

contract_type.reasoning: The document title states “Outsourcing Agreement,” which indicates the agreement type despite an internal definition referencing a supply agreement.

notice_period.reasoning: The agreement describes term and a one-time Renewal Term with certain termination notices (Section 18.1) but does not include an auto-renew provision requiring advance notice to prevent automatic renewal. Therefore, there is no specific “notice to prevent auto-renewal” period to extract.

expiration_date.raw_snippet: This Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall be valid until the [* * *] (the “Initial Term”).
expiration_date.reasoning: This clause sets the expiration as the end of the Initial Term, but the specific date/duration is redacted, so a precise date cannot be computed.
expiration_date.normalized_value: Initial Term ends on a redacted date (duration/date not disclosed)

renewal_term.raw_snippet: Should the Parties have not agreed to the following agreement by [* * *], this Agreement shall automatically stay in force for a maximum of [* * *] (unless otherwise mutually agreed by the Parties or as otherwise set forth in Section 18.1(a)) or until the Parties have signed the follow-on agreement (the “Renewal Term”).
renewal_term.reasoning: This sentence defines a Renewal Term that automatically continues for a maximum redacted period if no follow-on agreement is signed.
renewal_term.normalized_value: automatic continuation for a maximum (redacted) Renewal Term
